|YKOAuralis is a wandering prismatic sky continent intended for adventurers
around level 200 and above. Its level ranges are recommendations, not gates.

Reach Auralis aboard the |YKBPrismatic Wayfarer|YKO from the elevated berth at
DarkWind Port. The skyship accepts an ordinary ferry ticket. On arrival, touch
the wayshard in the Veil Below to unlock return travel through the wayshard
network.

Characters with a current means of flight can also reach Auralis through the
greater Aeolus sky. The prismatic wake lies west of the skies above Wayfare.
From that sky anchor, fly up beneath Solenne and land at the lower chain
harbor. The route is two-way; non-fliers cannot launch from the harbor, and
civic safety chains recover anyone whose flight ends in the open undercity air.

The lower city includes chainworks, moving counterweights, living rootworks,
a liquid-light cistern, memorial, bell foundry, lantern exchange, cloudwatch,
an old civic dragon roost, and multiple routes back into the original Veil.

The inhabited layers of Solenne are protected by a golden ward. Beyond them,
the |YKBShifting Spectrum|YKO cycles through Crimson, Azure, Emerald, Violet,
and Golden phases every fifteen minutes. Exposed wilderness can burn, freeze,
shock, or distort travelers; Golden light offers a brief recovery outside
combat. Grounded prism shelters block every phase hazard.

While in Auralis, type |YKBspectrum|YKO to see the current phase, the time until
it changes, and whether your location is protected.

Far above the first Crimson shelters, fixed shadows converge on the hidden
First Impact Scar. Its prism vanes teach the same controls used against
Vaelkor, the Ash Regent. During that encounter, threat messages name a vane
and give an exact response window. Use |YKBvanes|YKO for plain-text status,
|YKBturn <direction> vane toward Vaelkor|YKO to reflect a breath attack, and
|YKBshatter core|YKO before a suspended ember core heals him. Missed counters
deal damage but never stun or suppress commands.
